&gt; 1)What is meant by max-hops and max-depth in cxml file? Please explain.

Number of hops, i.e. &quot;traversed links of any type&quot;, beyond which a url
is considered out of scope.
http://builds.archive.org/javadoc/heritrix-3.1.0/org/archive/modules/deciderules/TooManyHopsDecideRule.html

&gt; 2)II have configure duplication reduction processor in Heritrix 3.1.0. When I analyzed crawl log. I have following entries.

What version of wayback are you using? I think it should support 304
revisit records, but we don&#39;t exercise that functionality much at the
archive.

You can set sendIfModifiedSince=false and sendIfNoneMatch=false on
FetchHTTP. Without those request headers, servers shouldn&#39;t respond
304s.

